{
  "text": "It is interesting to compare the results of our analysis with studies of collections of texts written in Portuguese and English, whose sizes ranged between 169 and 276425 words [CITATION_1] ). The representation of texts used in [CITATION_2] ) corresponds to P-space in our classification. However, unlike our investigation, a network of concepts has also been considered in [CITATION_3] ) and could form the basis for a future study of fables. The quantitative characteristics of the corresponding network are \u03b3 = 1.6 \u00b1 0.2, l = 2.0 \u00b1 0.1, l max = 4 \u00b1 1, C = 0.83 \u00b1 0.03 and are in a good agreement with our results (\u03b3 = 2.0, l = 2.25, l max = 5, C = 0.818 for the combination of two fables). Such agreement is interesting, not only because the investigated networks correspond to different languages (English, Portuguese in Caldeira et al. (2006) and Ukrainian in our case), but mainly because it shows that the restriction to the specific subset of words (words-concepts) does not cause significant changes in the above-considered features of a language network.",
  "citation_candidates": [
